            <title>[SPARK-2552] Stabilize the computation of logistic function in pyspark</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2552</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;exp(1000) throws an error in python. For logistic function, we can use either 1 / ( 1 + exp( -x ) ) or 1 - 1 / (1 + exp( x ) ) to compute its value which ensuring exp always takes a negative value.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
